\begin_layout Definition
Proposition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
A proposition is a declarative sentence (a sentence declares a fact) that
 is either true or false but not both, which can be represented by a proposition
al variable, conventionally 
\begin_inset Formula $p,q,r,s$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

